claim.claim-text:
A method of characterizing a tension strength of a fillet bond (128) joining a stiffener component (308) to a skin component (302) of a test specimen (300), comprising the steps of:
placing the test specimen (300) in a testing apparatus (600);
fixedly positioning a stiffener component (308) of the test specimen (300);
engaging the skin component (302) at a pair of engagement locations (626) on opposite sides of the fillet bond (128);
applying a tension test load (500) to the fillet bond (128) at the engagement locations (626); and
substantially isolating the fillet bond (128) from asymmetric bending when applying the tension test load (500).
